author: kevaundray
content:
I dont think you can make the minimal preset the same as Mainnet because the minimal one is used for performance purposes.

I asked Dan a week or so ago about this and it would require you to rebuild the bindings because that constant is hardcoded at compile time

author: kevaundray
content: So its possible to have a minimal npm package and a Mainnet npm package, but thats quite messy imo

author: g11tech
content: yes it would be super messy,  but apart from spec tests, it effectively undermines using the minimal so the compile time setting is not ideal. i think the better UX would be to specify the values on init/loading the lib, but i am not sure how much work it would be to make them dynamic

author: kevaundray
content:
Its a property of the c library, so its a bit of effort to config that at runtime. I can look into solutions and get back to you
